title: For Sale:  Taurus PT 809C
postcontent:
Like new. Bought 2 years ago and only put about 200 rounds through it. Buyer pays for background check and transfer fee.

Taurus PT809 Compact 9MM Review:
The Taurus PT809 Compact 9mm makes for a great conceal carry firearm and fits nicely in the shooters hand. The finger grooves molded into the polymer frame make gripping the firearm very easy and comfortable. The 13-round magazine has a finger extended floor plate on it which also also for more comfort while shooting.

Along with the 13-round magazine, the PT809 also comes with an extended 17-round magazine with the extended floor plate and magazine adapter to fill the gap between the frame and floor plate made by the longer magazine.

The Taurus features and external manual safety, slide lock/release, and shrouded hammer.

WHAT COMES WITH THE TAURUS PT809?

The PT809 comes in a large carrying case and included in the case is the firearm, both the standard and extended magazine, magazine loader,the Taurus safety lock keys, owners manual, registration information, and a child safety lock. All around I find the Taurus PT809 Compact to be a great carry firearm.

The 9mm cartridge is a great round to carry on your person because it does allow for the framework of the firearm to be smaller compared to a .40S&W, or .45ACP.

The gun fits nicely in your hand and with the finger extended floor plates on the magazines, you don't ever have to worry about having your last finger not being on the grip of the gun. The manual safety is a large obvious feature that is easy to activate and deactivate.

One feature that is not so obvious is the shrouded hammer, it can still be pulled back for single action use but it fits snugly up into the slide of the gun to avoid any possible snags.

Along with being about to be fired using single action, the PT809 Compact is also a double action pistol. I would recommend this firearm as a conceal carry gun, because it is very comfortable for the user and with the extended magazine is great for anyone with large hands.

The shrouded hammer and Glock style take down bar make the gun slim, and good for unholstering without snags. Taurus made this firearm to be user friendly and is great for a wide variety of people.

title: For Sale:  Youre guns are not made of gold.
postcontent:
Day in and day out I check these listings and its always the same crap.

" I have this LNIB glock 19 that I want to sell for $750 or trade value of $1000, would like to get a M2 Browning in trade"

Thats how almost all of you label your guns. Yes, pistols are and can be expensive, but your glock WILL NEVER be worth $750. I dont care if YOU polished it, all those fancy mags will go great with the package, but youre not going to get what you paid for them either.

"Ill add 100 rounds of ammo for $80 more" Oh well thank fuck, cause I was having a super hard time finding blazer 9MM ammo. 

Something else. You guys treat 1911s like they are the end all be all of pistols. Get real. Theyre antiquated. The only reason people buy them is cause they are a 1911. Can they look nice? Yes. Can they be expensive, yes. But your walmart special 1911 isnt worth 700. It isnt worth 600, or 500. Its worth MAYBE 350, its used, get over it.

If it doesnt say SIG or Kimber on it, its pretty much junk with maybe a few other exceptions. These 22LR 1911s are even worse, I mean 22s are useless as it is, but then you put it on a staple like the 1911. Thanks.

Youre chinese weapons are shit. Period. End of story. Ive fired numerous chinese makes and they are all easily broken, easily jammed pieces of shit. 

I also loved the sudden price increase on the saigas. One guy here had one for 450 and had it listed for about 2-3 months then all the sudden he went to 650, then back down to 550 and maybe he sold it IDK. Point is, they dont sell. Saigas chambered in BOTH 12ga and 7.62 are trashy redneck hoosier weapons that people only buy because they have the AK frame. 

Someone on here wants something like 1600 for his saiga 12GA piece of shit. Let me tell you, I can spend 1200 on a FNH 12GA SLP and itll be more accurate, more reliable and better looking than your drum fed piece of shit made in russia. 

Now onto the hack jobs. I love looking at these people who have modified there guns and tell us how great it works, but dont say who did it work. If it wasnt done in a professional shop, you cant charge a professional premium or assume were going to take your word that you even know what youre doing. Your polished XDM isnt fancy, it isnt unique, it isnt something I couldnt do on my own. So, no, it isnt worth 300 more. Get real.

Magazines and your no name POS scopes do not add value at an exponential rate. If you are selling an AR15 with 10 PMags and are adding 100 in value because of the magazines, FUCK YOU. I can get them all day long at 9.95. I have no idea how well you treat your mags, maybe you drop them every reload to try and be delta force dan at the range. I have no idea, but youre not getting even 8 dollars per. They add maybe 3-4 dollars each to the value. 

You fucking tool bag trailer trash idiots need to realize youre selling USED hardware privately. If I wanted to pay close to retail, why wouldnt I just pony up 200 more and buy it ACTUALLY nib at the store and know how its been handled.

In short, Glock is NOT the "king" of pistols. Theyre entry level/mid level range AT BEST. I can outshoot any glock, any day with my Five SeveN or my FNS - 40, or the FNX - 45. Any day, any time, any ammo.

Glocks are great at what they are, cheap polymer pistols that anyone with above minimum wage can afford and take to the range. Nothing more. Sure, they can be used in competition and Im sure they have been, but YOUR glock hasnt been, and isnt going to be. 

Start listing quality stuff on here at the right price, and list the junk at the price it belongs. Glocks shouldnt be on here for more than 400, period. Just about anyone who works for the government can get one at LE price for like 375-450 NEW. I can go buy a 22 RIGHT NOW for 420, brand new, in FDE with 3 mags. 

And when you DO have something of quality, stop thinking its worth thousands. Seriously. There is/was a PS90 on here for like 1500. GET FUCKING REAL DUDE. It had 2 shitty 10 round mags, no one cares about that garbage.

Edit. For example, check out this jackass selling an "AR15 pistol" 


Hardened arms upper, SAA lower, 30rd magazine. Built this from gunbroker auction parts, all new at the time of purchase. Very fun to shoot.

Comes with sig brace.

Spelling errors and referring to this as "ak pistol" will be ignored. I only sell to educated gun owners who I know can be responsible. Sorry,
personal preference.

Make offer, no trades.

Had to pick a brand for the post, not a SW 

Get over yourself dude. That thing is worth maybe 350, assuming you even pieced it together properly. Second, its a fucking mini AK. It might be an AR15 platform, but its shooting an AK round. 7.62x39, if it was 7.62x51, id say differently. Also you say you only sell to "educated" gun owners. Well lets be honest, an educated man wont buy a pieced together hodgepodge from some guy on armslist. Ill go buy the real deal at the store that has a clean SN and comes with a warranty.

The hinged floor plate magazine has a four round capacity in standard calibers and a three round capacity in magnum calibers.

Receiver machined from solid-steel bar stock resulting in uniformity and strength.
Cylindrical receiver design provides a solid bedding area in the stock for consistent shot placement.
Recessed bolt face locks up inside the counter-bored breech of the barrel which is surrounded by the receiver, forming "three-rings-of-steel" enclosing the cartridge case head for unparalleled strength.
Integral extractor is set in a groove inside the rim of the bolt face, uniformly supporting the cartridge head.
